Cell["\<\
If you are dealing with a Hopflink, keep in mind that you might need to \
partition your array in two BEFORE trying to plot things. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9838946712833047`*^9, 
  3.9838946944078197`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e07c73e4-6f01-4065-98d7-\
67c6e0a97bae"],

Cell["\<\
List out the singularities and report each points\[CloseCurlyQuote] distance \
from the mean. \[LineSeparator]The distance from the mean should vary \
continuously from point to point. Spurious jumps or dips in the mean very \
likely indicates a knotty signal.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.983888008782843*^9, 
  3.983888094877214*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fcbc000f-86ff-47e3-934f-\
